UV PEP 508 ENVIRONMENT MARKERS — INVESTIGATION FINDINGS
========================================================
Date: 2026-06-03


1. CRATE/MODULE THAT OWNS MARKER PARSING
-----------------------------------------
Primary crate: crates/uv-pep508/
All marker logic lives inside the marker sub-module of that crate:

  crates/uv-pep508/src/marker/
  ├── mod.rs          – public re-exports
  ├── environment.rs  – MarkerEnvironment struct (holds python_version, sys_platform, etc.)
  ├── parse.rs        – recursive-descent grammar parser
  ├── tree.rs         – MarkerTree / MarkerExpression types + evaluate() / is_false()
  ├── algebra.rs      – Boolean algebra on marker BDDs (and/or/not/is_disjoint)
  ├── simplify.rs     – to_dnf() and CNF simplification
  └── lowering.rs     – canonical key names (CanonicalMarkerValueString, etc.)

There is NO separate crates/uv-markers crate. Everything is in crates/uv-pep508.

The crates/uv-resolver/ crate consumes these types for resolution-time filtering, and
crates/uv-pypi-types/ contains a thin ResolverMarkerEnvironment wrapper.


2. KEY TYPES
-------------
Located in crates/uv-pep508/src/marker/tree.rs:

  pub enum MarkerExpression {        // line 503
      Version {
          key: MarkerValueVersion,   // e.g. python_version / python_full_version
          specifier: VersionSpecifier,
      },
      VersionIn {
