       Ok(Requirement { ..., marker: marker.unwrap_or_default(), ... })  // lib.rs:1015

   `unwrap_or_default()` gives MarkerTree::TRUE for requirements with no marker.

   The parse call chain:
     parse_pep508_requirement (lib.rs:892)
       → marker::parse::parse_markers_cursor (parse.rs:654)
         → parse_marker_or (parse.rs:596)
           → parse_marker_and
             → parse_marker_expr (parse.rs:567)
               → parse_marker_key_op_value
                 → MarkerExpression node → MarkerTree::expression(marker_expr)

   BDD algebra is computed immediately: the interner interns the resulting
   MarkerTree as a node in the global BDD. Simplification (e.g. contradiction
   detection → FALSE) also happens immediately as part of BDD construction.

B. RESOLUTION TIME — markers gate which requirements PubGrub sees
   At resolution time, inside crates/uv-resolver/src/resolver/mod.rs, markers
   are evaluated to decide whether each dependency is included in the current
   resolution environment. See Section 4 for the exact code path.

   There is NO separate "install time" evaluation of PEP 508 markers in uv's
   resolver; the lockfile already records which packages survived marker
   filtering.


